  accentWord="Shopfitting"
  subhead="Your reel of a boutique shop transformation from shell to finished fit-out earns seven thousand views. A restaurant chain DMs about new site designs. Your AI responds while you install display units."
  scenario="It is 1am on a Saturday. A chef in Oxford has just finished service at the restaurant where he works. He has been planning his own place for two years and has finally secured the lease on a 1,800-square-foot unit in a Victorian building on St Clements. He has been browsing Instagram for shopfitters who understand hospitality — and finds your account. Your portfolio shows exactly what he wants: open kitchens with pass counters, exposed services as a design feature, and bespoke joinery that feels both industrial and refined. He DMs: 'Chef looking to open my own restaurant in OX4. Large unit, 1,800sqft, Victorian building. Want an open kitchen with a pass counter overlooking the dining room, exposed ductwork as a feature, banquette seating for 80 covers, and a small cocktail bar near the entrance. Budget is £150k for the fit-out. I have a concept deck I can send. Interested?' Without AI Instagram DMs, you see the DM Saturday afternoon. He contacted two other shopfitters; one responded at 8am with congratulations and a request for the concept deck. With AI DMs, the reply arrives at 1:01am: 'Congratulations on the new restaurant — hospitality fit-outs with open kitchens and exposed services are among our favourite projects. We would love to see the concept deck. Could you share it along with the unit address? One of our team will call you on Monday to discuss the scope and arrange a site walkthrough.' He uploads the concept deck. Saturday at 10am you open the lead: chef-owner restaurant, 1,800sqft Victorian, OX4, open kitchen with pass counter, exposed ductwork, 80-cover banquette, cocktail bar, £150k budget, concept deck attached. You call Monday at 9am."
  benefits={benefits}
